title: For Weary Georgia Voters, Senate Runoff Brings a Sense of Déjà Vu
description: The candidates will have to deal with a mix of enthusiasm and fatigue among Georgia voters as they charge into the state’s third Senate runoff in two years.
dc:creator: Richard Fausset, Rick Rojas and Sean Keenan

media:content.media:credit: Nicole Craine for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: Voters casting their ballots in Atlanta on Tuesday. The runoff election for the Georgia Senate race is scheduled for Dec. 6.
